[Features]
- Allow specifying namespace for each editor
- Modify `sys.excepthook` or maybe pyodide config to give error tracebacks more similar to a typical python interpreter
- Allow importing from multiple files
    - make relative imports look for a relative src address
    - allow importing from the namespace of another editor on the page
- Allow Ctrl + C to interrupt, signal to kill, possibly signal to pause

[Fundamental Issues]
- get input function working when using webworker
- Auto-warn if code contains threading, time.sleep, or other features/libraries not currently supported
- fix or possibly work around time.sleep (pyodide issue)

[IDE-type features]
- Add in linting for common syntax errors
- Add in however help tooltips and typehinting

[JS/CSS]
- Make message bar sticky but only within the bounds of the parent element
- Add Ctrl+s to download a `.py` file
- Use cookies to save configs, not sure if this will work in StackOverflow environment
- Add a bug reporting link

[Things to test]
- Flask
- multiprocessing


